# SeatUp.io Backend
## Setup
1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and edit with your database and secret values.
2. Run database migration (see userModel.js for SQL).
3. Install dependencies: `npm install`
4. Seed admin user: `npm run seed`
5. Start API server: `npm start`
## API Routes
- `POST /api/auth/register` — Register user
- `POST /api/auth/login` — Authenticate user, returns JWT
- `GET /api/user/me` — Get own user info (JWT required)
- `GET /api/user/:id` — Get user info by id (admin/hr only)
_Connect frontend login with `POST /api/auth/login`._
